Package: NYWinterMaltingBarley
Title: Genomic and Phenomic Prediction in NY Winter Malting Barley
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Siim", "Sepp", email = "s11ms3pp@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Reproducible analysis pipeline for predicting agronomic and
    malt quality traits in the NY Winter Malting Barley breeding program.
    Integrates UAV multispectral imagery, Barley 50K SNP genotype data,
    and multi-year field phenotypes across five environments (2021-2025).
    Prediction approaches include phenomic prediction, GBLUP, multi-trait
    GBLUP, double-kernel models, and deep neural network synthetic VIs.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    asreml,
    ASRgenomics,
    ASRtriala,
    rrBLUP,
    caret,
    glmnet,
    dplyr,
    tidyr,
    ggplot2,
    readr,
    readxl,
    workflowr
